Yes — the fix is to skip the XSS query validation for framework/static resource requests before your query-string checks run.

Right now your filter is probably inspecting requests like:
	•	javax.faces.resource/...
	•	rfRes/...
	•	a4j/...
	•	popup panel CSS/JS resource URLs
	•	framework-generated requests with params like db=...

When those get blocked, the browser receives an HTML error page instead of CSS/JS, and the page hangs at 99%.

Fix approach

Do this in matchExcludePattern(...):
	1.	Detect JSF / RichFaces / A4J static resource requests first
	2.	Return true immediately for those
	3.	Only run your XSS query validation for real business page requests

⸻

Recommended code change

Add this helper method to IPSCustRegSessionFilter:

private boolean isFrameworkResourceRequest(HttpServletRequest hsr) {
    String requestUri = hsr.getRequestURI();
    String servletPath = hsr.getServletPath();

    if (requestUri == null) {
        requestUri = "";
    }
    if (servletPath == null) {
        servletPath = "";
    }

    return requestUri.contains("javax.faces.resource")
            || requestUri.contains("/rfRes/")
            || requestUri.contains("/a4j/")
            || servletPath.contains("javax.faces.resource")
            || servletPath.contains("/rfRes/")
            || servletPath.contains("/a4j/");
}

Then update your matchExcludePattern(...) like this:

private boolean matchExcludePattern(HttpServletRequest hsr, NameValueVo nv) throws SecurityException {

    String[] excludePatternsArr = excludePatterns.split(",");
    String requestUri = hsr.getRequestURI();
    String servletPath = hsr.getServletPath();
    String queryString = hsr.getQueryString();

    nv.setBooleanValue(false);

    // ---------------------------------------------------
    // 1. BYPASS FRAMEWORK / STATIC RESOURCE REQUESTS
    // ---------------------------------------------------
    if (isFrameworkResourceRequest(hsr)) {
        return true;
    }

    // ---------------------------------------------------
    // 2. EXISTING EXCLUDE PATTERN LOGIC
    // ---------------------------------------------------
    if (excludePatternsArr != null) {
        for (String pattern : excludePatternsArr) {
            if (pattern != null) {
                pattern = pattern.trim();
                if (!pattern.isEmpty()) {
                    if ((servletPath != null && servletPath.startsWith(pattern))
                            || (requestUri != null && requestUri.contains(pattern))) {
                        return true;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }

    // ---------------------------------------------------
    // 3. QUERY PARAMETER VALIDATION
    //    ONLY FOR NON-RESOURCE / BUSINESS REQUESTS
    // ---------------------------------------------------
    if (StringUtils.isNotBlank(queryString)) {

        String[] pairs = queryString.split("&");
        for (String pair : pairs) {
            if (pair == null || pair.isEmpty()) {
                continue;
            }

            int eqIdx = pair.indexOf('=');
            String name = (eqIdx >= 0) ? pair.substring(0, eqIdx) : pair;
            String valuePart = (eqIdx >= 0 && eqIdx + 1 < pair.length())
                    ? pair.substring(eqIdx + 1)
                    : "";

            String decodedValue;
            try {
                decodedValue = URLDecoder.decode(valuePart, StandardCharsets.UTF_8.name());
            } catch (IllegalArgumentException ex) {
                CustomLogger.warn(this.getClass(),
                        "Malformed encoding in query parameter '" + name + "': " + valuePart);
                throw new SecurityException("Invalid query string encoding detected.");
            } catch (UnsupportedEncodingException ex) {
                CustomLogger.warn(this.getClass(),
                        "Unsupported encoding in query parameter '" + name + "': " + valuePart);
                throw new SecurityException("Invalid query string encoding detected.");
            }

            // basic max length guard
            if (decodedValue != null && decodedValue.length() > 2048) {
                CustomLogger.warn(this.getClass(),
                        "Param '" + name + "' exceeded max length: " + decodedValue.length());
                throw new SecurityException("Invalid query parameter value detected.");
            }

            // global XSS checks
            if (decodedValue != null
                    && (DANGEROUS_CHARS.matcher(decodedValue).find()
                    || SUSPICIOUS_KEYWORDS.matcher(decodedValue).find())) {
                CustomLogger.warn(this.getClass(),
                        "Potential XSS attack in param '" + name + "': " + decodedValue);
                throw new SecurityException("Potential XSS attack detected.");
            }

            // optional strict validation only for do/cmd
            if ("do".equals(name) || "cmd".equals(name)) {
                if (decodedValue == null || !DO_CMD_VALUE_PATTERN.matcher(decodedValue).matches()) {
                    CustomLogger.warn(this.getClass(),
                            "do/cmd param failed validation: " + decodedValue);
                    throw new SecurityException("Invalid do/cmd value detected.");
                }
            }
        }

        nv.setBooleanValue(true);
    }

    return false;
}


⸻

Why this fix works

This prevents your filter from interfering with framework resource loading such as:
	•	JS files
	•	CSS files
	•	RichFaces popup resources
	•	Ajax framework resources

So the browser will get actual CSS/JS again instead of your HTML error page.

⸻

If you want the quickest minimal fix

If you do not want to add a helper method, add this near the top of matchExcludePattern(...):

String requestUri = hsr.getRequestURI();
if (requestUri != null &&
        (requestUri.contains("javax.faces.resource")
        || requestUri.contains("/rfRes/")
        || requestUri.contains("/a4j/"))) {
    return true;
}

That alone may immediately fix the 99% issue.

